column40: There's a bit of a trend developing among wine collectors where aged wine has become a major theme. This Aged Cabernet wine club is unusual and ought to satisfy Cali Cab lovers everywhere.
column41: We like that they bring you a variety of aged Cabernets, at different levels of quality from exceptional to rarified. While your monthly shipment price will vary, so will the different terroirs and winemaker expression of the king of all varietals.
column42: While we get the sense that you'll always pay a fair price for the wines you're being sent, the price range offered and lack of clear proclamation of that fact makes just a teeny bit nervous.

column40: A rare wine club focusing only on Bordeaux wines from France. If you are or know a Bordeaux lover who doesn't love Bordeaux prices, this is a no-brainer decision.
column41: For most American consumers, buying French wine is scary and risky. By joining a Bordeaux wine club you can learn about Bordeaux wines without all of the risk because you know the wine club has picked out excellent wines.
column42: We'd like them to publish what wines they've shipped to customers in the past and we'd like it if the website were more user-friendly.

column40: Australia and New Zealand produce some of the world's finest wines, and often at a bargain when compared to their US counterparts. column42: We'd love to see a gift option (pre-paid subscription) because this would make an excellent gift for an Italian wine lover.
column43: INTRODUCTORY OFFER — Six top-quality Italian wines for only $39.90! Plus 1 wooden Wine Box with wine accessories & an extra bottle of fine Italian wine. Free tasting notes and binder, too.

column17: Introductory offer: Free professional corkscrew, a $20 value
column40: It's easy to be a Pinotphile, but there are so many interesting alternatives that there's no reason to limit yourself. This club features one Pinot Noir and one similarly-styled red wine each month.
column41: Plonk took their winning model for finding and delivering interesting wines at exceptional value, and then figured out how to make it even better with a mix of familiar and adventure in every box.
column42: We'd love to see a buy-more-save-more option and even a 4-bottle version for customers who just can't get enough of their killer curation.
column43: Get a FREE double-hinged corkscrew with your first shipment. If you've never used one, you'll see why it's the best way to open a bottle of wine!
